leadership-approach|vision_results_process_people|application_1|1|Start with the reason and direction|Start by giving the work a clear reason and direction. Name what the current decision is meant to make possible, then connect that future frame to one practical action people can take now.|vision|active|leadership-approach::vision_results_process_people::application_1
leadership-approach|vision_results_process_people|application_2|2|Stabilise with Results, then add Process|Before you move on, use Results to turn the conversation into a named decision, owner, and follow-up point. Then bring in Process to turn intent into steps, responsibilities, and a cleaner handover. This gives the work a stronger middle step before you rely on the full pattern.|results|active|leadership-approach::vision_results_process_people::application_2
leadership-approach|vision_results_process_people|application_3|3|Bring in People when the work tightens|When the work starts to narrow, bring in People deliberately. In practice, speak with the people most affected and clarify what they need to know, trust, or contribute. Do this before the first two signals have answered the problem so completely that the wider need is harder to see.|people|active|leadership-approach::vision_results_process_people::application_3
